 in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Einion","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of <b>Pinning</b> (see   Penning  ) with <i>-ion</i> substituted for <i>-in(g)</i>, perhaps through false association with the word <i>pinion</i> ‘wing, feather’. Compare   Pinyan  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Penning","meanings":["English, Dutch, and North German: from early Middle English <i>penning</i>, Low German <i>penning</i>, Middle Dutch <i>penninc</i> ‘penny’ (see   Penny  ), a topographic name (from a field name) or a nickname referring to tax dues of a penny.","South German: from the short form, <i>Panno</i>, of an ancient Germanic personal name derived from a word meaning ‘ban, order, command’.","English: from a Middle English personal name <i>Pening</i>, <i>Pining</i>, presumably representing an unrecorded Old English name, a pet form perhaps of <i>Penda</i> or of names like <i>Pendhere</i> and <i>Pendwulf</i>."]},{"name":"Pinyan","meanings":["English: variant of   Pinion  ."]}]},{"name":"Gronwy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name of uncertain derivation, borne in the <i>Mabinogi</i> by  Goronwy the Staunch , Lord of Penllyn. He became the lover of the flower-maiden Blodeuedd and murdered her husband  Lleu Llaw Gyffes , but Lleu was later restored to life and definitively dispatched Goronwy."],"variants":[{"name":"Gronw","meanings":["Variant of   Goronwy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Gronwy ap Einion was born about 1000, in Llandyfeisant, Carmarthenshire, Wales. He had at least 2 sons with Aethelflaeda Ferch Eadwine of Mercia. He died in Flintshire, Wales."},"et":{"about 1000–":"umbes 1000–Surnud","1000–1044":"1000–1044","1020–1073":"1020–1073","1022–Male":"1022–Surnud","1000–Male":"1000–Surnud","1022":"1022","1044":"1044","1000":"1000","1020":"1020","1073":"1073","about 1020":"umbes 1020","about 1000":"umbes 1000","about 1022":"umbes 1022","of Cilcen,Betws-yn-Rhos,Denbighshire,Wales":"Betws-yn-rhos, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Llandyfeisant, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llandyfeisant, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Tegeingl, Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1000–":"noin 1000–Kuollut","1000–1044":"1000–1044","1020–1073":"1020–1073","1022–Male":"1022–Kuollut","1000–Male":"1000–Kuollut","1022":"1022","1044":"1044","1000":"1000","1020":"1020","1073":"1073","about 1020":"noin 1020","about 1000":"noin 1000","about 1022":"noin 1022","of Cilcen,Betws-yn-Rhos,Denbighshire,Wales":"Betws-yn-rhos, Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Llandyfeisant, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llandyfeisant, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Tegeingl, Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1000–":"environ 1000–Décédé","1000–1044":"1000–1044","1020–1073":"1020–1073","1022–Male":"1022–Décédé","1000–Male":"1000–Décédé","1022":"1022","1044":"1044","1000":"1000","1020":"1020","1073":"1073","about 1020":"environ 1020","about 1000":"environ 1000","about 1022":"environ 1022","of Cilcen,Betws-yn-Rhos,Denbighshire,Wales":"Betws-yn-rhos, Denbighshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Llandyfeisant, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Llandyfeisant, Carmarthenshire, Galles","Tegeingl, Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Galles","Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Gronwy ap Ei